<h3 id="fieldedge-mobile">3. FieldEdge Mobile</h3>

<p>FieldEdge mobile targets larger HVAC companies with complex inventory management needs. The app shines for technicians who handle parts ordering, warranty claims, and detailed service documentation.</p>

<p><strong>Enterprise Features:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Real-time inventory tracking across multiple trucks and warehouses</li>
<li>Manufacturer warranty claim submission with photo documentation</li>
<li>Detailed labor tracking with task-specific time codes</li>
<li>Equipment history access with previous service records</li>
<li>Advanced reporting with technician performance metrics</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Best For:</strong> Companies with 15+ technicians who need detailed inventory control and performance tracking. Smaller companies often find FieldEdge overly complex.</p>

<p><strong>Pricing:</strong> Starts at $89/month per user. No transaction fees for payment processing but requires annual contracts.</p>

<h3 id="refrigerant-apps">4. HVAC Check & Charge (Free)</h3>

<p>The most downloaded HVAC-specific app with over 380,000 installs. HVAC Check & Charge focuses purely on refrigerant calculations and system diagnostics, making it an essential supplement to business management apps.</p>

<p><strong>Calculator Functions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Superheat and subcooling calculations for 70+ refrigerants</li>
<li>Target temperature calculations based on ambient conditions</li>
<li>Refrigerant charge calculations by system type and tonnage</li>
<li>Pressure-temperature charts with altitude adjustments</li>
<li>Troubleshooting guides for common system issues</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Why It Works:</strong> Technicians report 23% fewer callbacks when using the app's diagnostic workflows. The offline functionality means calculations work even in basements or areas with poor cell coverage.</p>

<p><strong>Pricing:</strong> Free with optional Pro version at $9.99/year for advanced features.</p>

<h3 id="manual-apps">5. ServiceTitan Mobile</h3>

<p>ServiceTitan's mobile app represents the premium end of HVAC software. While expensive and complex, it offers unmatched integration with marketing, accounting, and customer management systems.</p>

<p><strong>Advanced Capabilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Complete customer history with previous service photos and notes</li>
<li>Dynamic pricing with real-time profit margin calculations</li>
<li>Maintenance agreement management with automated scheduling</li>
<li>Comprehensive reporting accessible from mobile devices</li>
<li>Integration with 200+ third-party tools and suppliers</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Reality Check:</strong> ServiceTitan mobile requires extensive training (40+ hours) and works best for companies doing $2M+ annual revenue. Implementation costs range from $15,000-50,000.</p>

<p>For detailed pricing information, see our <a href="/hvac/pricing/servicetitan-pricing">complete ServiceTitan pricing guide</a>.</p>

